Most AI benchmarks test memorization.

ARC-AGI, built on @fchollet's definition of intelligence, tests how efficiently models learn new skills — tasks humans solve in 1–2 tries, but even state-of-the-art LLMs still fail.

@GregKamradt joined me on @VanishingData to explain why... https://t.co/fGxL4t2rAO
